          ]
        }
      },
      "feedback": {
        "correct": "Exactly — raise each exponent, divide by the new exponent, then finish with $+ C$.",
        "incorrect": "You must raise the exponent before you can divide by the new one, and $C$ comes last.",
        "hint": "Raise the power, divide by the new power, then add $C$."
      }
    },
    {
